The 3rd edition of EMWA – Equipment & Manufacturing West Africa is to hold from 30 May – 01 June 2023 at the Landmark Centre Lagos, the Nigerian-Indonesian Chamber of Commerce and Industry has announced. According to the Chamber, “Nigerians have an opportunity to concentrate on local manufacturing, reduce our reliance on imported goods, and strengthen our manufacturing infrastructure during these unsettling times in the global economy.” It said the event is “a platform to showcase your innovative products and services and forge enduring business connections, EMWA is the ideal event to exhibit at and make a real impact”. “Over the course of its successful editions, EMWA has united over 5,000 manufacturing professionals and attracted over 130 prominent brands from across the country and globe,” the Chamber said.